You should explicitly set the action command for the &quot;submit&quot; button.
Like this:
```
JButton submit = new JButton(&quot;Submit values&quot;);
submit.addActionListener(this);
submit.setActionCommand(&quot;submit&quot;);
```
Remember, you should set an action command for a `Component`(refers to `JButton` here) before it could pass the action command to the `ActionEvent`.

Try declaring an anonymous inner class, this will create an action listener just for your button. Additionally this will be useful if you decide to add more buttons in the future, since you could just declare a new class for each button. 
Just remember to define submitButtonPressed() later.

Your code would look like this:

        JButton submit = new JButton(&quot;Submit values&quot;);
        addActionListener(new ActionListener() {
            @Override
            public void actionPerformed(ActionEvent e) {
                submitButtonPressed();
            }
        });

